5|$|Rivadavias genesis can {{be traced}} to the naval <b>arms</b> <b>races</b> between Chile and Argentina which were spawned by {{territorial}} disputes over their mutual borders in Patagonia and Puna de Atacama, along with control of the Beagle Channel. These <b>arms</b> <b>races</b> flared up in the 1890s and again in 1902; the latter was eventually stopped through British mediation. Provisions in the dispute-ending treaty imposed restrictions on both countries' navies. The United Kingdom's Royal Navy bought the two Constitución-class pre-dreadnought battleships that were being built for Chile, and Argentina sold its two Rivadavia-class armored cruisers under construction in Italy to Japan.|$|R
